Right listen up...

The QW 757 and AS 320 will not be around here for a LONG time. I know because I was one of the people that used to put stuff here for you guys (had account removed....long story).

The AS uses a new type of live protection that's going to take a long time to come up with a work around for. Sad but true.

The QW 757 uses the essellerate protection that you might recognise form the cloud9 and FSDT sceneries. You'll remember how long these took to crack in the first place so expect it to take that long again. Infact the latest FSDT scenery 'las vegas' is still to be properly cracked for FS9.

So your options are either to wait it out however long it might be or to go and buy them unfortunately. 

There's NO point in keeping requesting them though as the cracked software just doesn't exist yet. I promise you that within a week or so of it being cracked it will end up on TPB. Just don't know when that will be.

The big difference is the wx engine in here and perhaps that damn low level fog can be mitigated using REX's engine. REX also supports updates from the VATSIM wx servers.
